Oat Meal Cookies

1 cup butter, softened
1 & 1/2 cup white sugar
2 eggs
2 cups all-purpose flour
1 teaspoon baking soda (or 2 teaspoons baking powder)
1 teaspoon salt
3 cups oats
1 teaspoon vanilla extract (optional)
1â€‰& 1/2 teaspoons ground cinnamon (optional)

Mix the flour, baking soda, salt together.
Mix in one egg at a time
Mix in the oats
Mix in butter

Mix until forms a nice dough

Leave in fridge for one hour.

Preheat oven to 375F (190C)
Make walnut sized balls from dough and place evenly on a greased glass or metal pan (foil works too)
Flatten each
Bake for 8-10 minutes
Let cool
